<tr>
<td colspan="3">
<div id="sectionDescription">This guide provides a brief introduction to adding 3D objects to an Open Wonderland scene and using the editing tools to arrange them.</div>
</td>
</tr>

<tr>

<td>
<div id="step">
<img src="BlueNumbers/Blue-1.png" align="top">
Create or find a 3D object in .kmz or .dae format. Drag and drop the file into a Wonderland scene.
<div id="pix"><img src="ArrangingObjects/Scene-drop-crp3.png" width="225px"></div>
The object you drop in will appear directly in front of your avatar, unless it is very large. In that case, it will surround you instead.
</div>
</td>

<td>
<div id="step">
<img src="BlueNumbers/Blue-2.png" align="top">
If the object appears too dark, right click and select "Properties..."
<div id="pix"><img src="ArrangingObjects/Scene-PropertiesMenu-crp.png" width="225px"></div>
In the Object Editor window that  opens, select the "Model Component" capability, uncheck "Lighting Enabled," and click "Apply." Close the Object Editor window.
</div>
</td>

<td>
<div id="step">
<img src="BlueNumbers/Blue-3.png" align="top">
Right click on the object again and select "Edit" from the context menu.
<div id="pix"><img src="ArrangingObjects/Scene-EditMoveUp-crp.png" width="225px"></div>
Red, green, and blue move tools will appear on the object and an Edit Object palette will open. Drag on the green arrow to move the object up and down. Drag on the red and blue arrows to move the object back, forth, right, and left.
</div>
</td>
</tr>

<tr>

<td>
<div id="step">
<img src="BlueNumbers/Blue-4.png" align="top">
Object Edit palette.
<div id="pix"><img src="ArrangingObjects/EditPalette.png" width="225px"></div>
<div id="stepNoHang">
<br>
Here's what each icon in the palette does:<br><br>
<img width="22px" src="ArrangingObjects/TranslateIcon.png" align="center"> Move<br>
<img width="22px" src="ArrangingObjects/RotateIcon.png" align="center"> Rotate<br>
<img width="22px" src="ArrangingObjects/ScaleIcon.png" align="center"> Scale<br>
<br>
<img src="ArrangingObjects/AffordanceSlider.png"><br>
<br>
The Affordance Size slider makes the tools themselves bigger or smaller.<br>
<br>
<img src="ArrangingObjects/DetailsButton.png"><br>
<br>
The Details button opens the Details pane, shown next.
</div>
</td>


<td>
<div id="step">
<img src="BlueNumbers/Blue-5.png" align="top">
Sometimes it is difficult to move an object in all directions using the move tools, especially if one of the arrows is pointing straight towards you. If this is the case, click "Details..." to open the Details Pane. 
<div id="pix"><img src="ArrangingObjects/Scene-EditClickClose-crp3.png" height="200px">
<img src="ArrangingObjects/DetailsPane.png" height="200px" hspace="10"></div>
<div id="stepNoHang">
Use the spinners (small up and down arrows) to change the values. The first set of numbers moves the object, the second set governs rotation, and the bottom value controls scale. You may also type values into the fields.
</div>
</div>
</td>

<td>
<div id="step">
<img src="BlueNumbers/Blue-6.png" align="top">
To rotate the object, select the Rotate tool. Rotation bands will appear around the object.
<div id="pix"><img src="ArrangingObjects/Scene-EditRotate-crp.png" width="225px"></div>
Click and drag on the red, green, and blue bands to rotate the object in different directions. You can use a combination of the in-world tools and the Details pain to make fine adjustments. 
<br><br>
Clicking again on the Rotate tool hides the bands.
</div>
</td>
</tr>

<tr>

<td>
<div id="step">
<img src="BlueNumbers/Blue-7.png" align="top">
To resize the object, select the Resize tool. A translucent black sphere will appear around the object.
<div id="pix"><img src="ArrangingObjects/Scene-EditEnlarge-crp2.png" width="225px"></div>
Click and drag on the sphere towards the center of the object to make it smaller. Drag away from the center to enlarge it. 
<br>
<br>
Clicking again on the Resize tool hides the sphere.</div>
</td>

<td>
<div id="step">
<img src="BlueNumbers/Blue-8.png" align="top">
When finished positioning an object, click on the red "X" to close the edit palette.
<div id="pix"><img src="ArrangingObjects/Scene-EditClickClose-crp2.png" width="225px"></div>
<div id="stepNoHang">
This will also close the Details pane and hide any visible in-world tools.
<br><br>
You can now add more objects to your scene or select other objects to move and resize. <br>
<br>
<img src="ArrangingObjects/Scene-Complete3-crp2.png" width="225px"><br>
<br>
Make it a collaborative experience by inviting others into your world to help you create the scene.
</div>
</td>


<!--       TIPS SECTION -->
<td>
<div id="sectionHead">Tips</div>

<div id="tipName">Finding Art</div>
<div id="tip">The easiest place to find free 3D models for Wonderland worlds is the <a href="http://sketchup.google.com/3dwarehouse/">Google 3D Warehouse</a>. There are even some Open Wonderland collections which you can find by typing "Wonderland" into the search field and selecting "Collections" from the search menu.  </div>

<div id="tipName">Creating Your Own Art</div>
<div id="tip">You can use any 3D modeling tool that can export to the COLLADA format (either .kmz or .dae format files). The easiest 3D modeling tool to learn is <a href="http://sketchup.google.com/intl/en/">Google SketchUp</a>, a free tool for Windows and Macs.
</div>

<div id="tipName">Adding Other Content</div>
<div id="tip">Dragging and dropping images (.jpg, .png, or .gif) into a world is a quick way to add content. In addition to wall hangings, you can use photos as floor tiles, rugs, or backdrops for outside open windows. PDF documents may also be dropped into the world, as can videos if you have the video module installed. You can also populate your space with 2D and 3D apps installed on your server by selecting "Object" from the Insert menu.
</div>

</td>

</tr>
